Xanadu - The World's Only Hope
Xanadu - The Surprise, Part 1 of 3

by Kevin Schaeffer

You are Xanadu Magoo.  You're not much to look at and your strength rivals that of an adolescent gerbil.  What you lack in strength and good looks you sort of make up for in intelligence.  Your IQ is above average, registering in at a mighty 101.    You are a science teacher at the "prestigeous" Lady of the Holy Moly Incapables.  You have an interest in physics and chemistry and the ladies, but none of them have shown you any love back.  But enough about you... let's get to your adventure!

Dr. Marcus Straussberger, an old high school friend (more like an acquaintance, but you'll take what you can get), has recruited you to go on a mission with him.  Dr. Dingo, a rogue military agent sits atop the most wanted list and he continues to escape the US government.  His last known whereabouts were somewhere deep in the desert several continents away.  You have been convinced that he is no longer there, but "Strauss" needs your help analyzing the science doohickies in his vacated compound.  You now find yourself in the backseat of an army issued ATV riding to your destination.

Good luck.
You are in a back seat.

You are riding in the backseat of a military issued Land Rover.  Sitting on the seat to your left is Marcus Straussberger, a childhood friend and military superhero.

There is a console separating the two of you.

> wait

> wait
Time passes.
> wait

> wait
Time passes.
> wait

> wait
Time passes.

The driver seems to be speeding up...

> wait

> wait
Time passes.
> wait

> wait
Time passes.

The car suddenly jerks back and forth unnaturally.  You look up at the driver and he seems to be nervous, checking his mirrors and looking over his shoulder frequently.

> wait

> wait
Time passes.
> wait

> wait
Time passes.

You look out the windows of the vehicle and notice that a car is trailing you.  One man sticks his head out of the car and you notice he has a rocket launcher!

> wait

> wait
Time passes.

You see the stranger in the vehicle pull the trigger and a rocket fires from the launcher.  Just before it hits your vehicle, the drivers yanks the wheel hard left, the rocket just sailing behind your vehicle!

> wait

> wait
Time passes.

For a brief moment you felt like you dodged a bullet... literally.  But, in the next instance, you realize you are airborne.  Seconds pass as minutes and finally you crash nose first into the unforgiving earth.  The rover is exploding and crashing in all around you at the same time.  You're not sure how far your vehicle had careened down the side of this cliff but after the third tumble down the cliff's side, you lose consciousness and everything goes black...

You are on a Rocky Outcropping.

You open your eyes and see smoke trailing up into the sky.  The Land Rover is perched twenty to thirty feet up on a cut in the cliff.  Inside the burning vehicle is the remains of the driver, who at this stage is most certainly dead.  The vehicle is far too high for you to do anything about.  In fact, you might want to scoot your scrawny little butt out of here before you waste any more time.  You heard a car door slam shut followed by some men speaking in an unknown, but sinister sounding language.

On the ground you see a large belt.

You could, if you were careful, scamper down the cliff's face.

You seem to have lost all of your possessions in the crash.  You better start accumulating more of them.  Fortunately those items probably weren't important in your quest.

> look at belt

> look at belt
It is a standard belt for a bigger man.  In fact, you think this belt might have belonged to Strauss.  You can't wear it, but you could carry it around if it makes you feel better.
Attached to the belt you see a knife and a lasso.
> take knife

> take knife
Careful, Emeril!  Don't cut yourself!  Knife taken.
> take lasso

> take lasso
Just a natural Indiana Jones, huh?  Lasso taken.
> down

> down

You are on a Narrow Ledge.

Perching on this precipitous and perilous precipice is probably poor planning.  Perhaps you should prohibit perusing prior to your peril?

The narrow ledge continues to wind around the cliff side to the south or you could retreat back up the cliff to the northeast.  You notice there is a small crack behind you to the west.

> west

> west

You turn sideways and squeeze through the dark, narrow opening in the cliff wall.

You are in a Small Cave.

This is a very small cave.  Through the wall to the east extends a tiny sliver of light that extends just beyond the rock wall.

If you suck in your gut, you may be able to squeeze through the tiny crack on the east wall.

The sliver of light seems to have crept a bit across the cave floor.

Yep.  The sliver of light is definitely moving.  It is nearly to the back of the small cave.

The sliver of light has now extended all of the way across the floor of the cave.  You follow the light to the back of the cave and notice a glint reflecting back at you.
> look at glint

> look at glint
Upon closer inspection, the light is glimmering off of a a shovel.
> take shovel

> take shovel
You retrieve the shovel.
