You are in an Archeological Site.

It looks like this archaeological dig site has been vacated recently.  About twenty smaller areas have already been excavated.  These small holes in the ground are all empty and they vary in size from knee deep to small swimming pool size.  The dirt removed from the holes is piled up next to each hole.

There is undisturbed ground here, too.  The undisturbed ground is expansive to say the least.  It probably stretches out in an area that is five or six hundred meters square.  The ground in this area is hard and slightly discolored in spots.

There are exits far off to the east, southeast, and north.

> east

> east

You are in a Quarry.

There is a large rock here.

You are in a mining quarry.  There are boarded up mines in every direction except to the west.  The eastern-most mine looks newly boarded over because the planks look newer and less weathered.
> look at planks

> look at planks
The planks are attached loosely to the mine's threshold by some nails that look like they were hammered in very quickly with a soft hammer.
> use knife on nails

> use knife on nails
You widdle away at each nail until the nail pops out of the wood and falls to the ground.  It takes some time but eventually,  you end up with a pile of planks at your feet and an open mine entrance to the east.
> east

> east

You are in a Chasm.

This is a small abandoned mine.  It has probably been abandoned due to the massive chasm that runs across the center of the floor.  The opposite side of the small mine is visible from your vantage point.  It looks like there is something drilled into the wall on the other side of the mine. There is a hook on the other side of the chasm.

> use sticky lasso on dirty key

> use sticky lasso on dirty key
You lash out with the sticky lasso at the key.  The rope end is a bit heavier than you expect, but after a few tries you manage to slap the lasso on to the key that is hanging on the wall across the chasm.  You pull the rope (and the key) across the chasm to your half of the mine.
> take dirty key

> take dirty key
You have succesfully retrieved the key from the far side of the chasm.  Well done!
> drop sticky lasso

> drop sticky lasso
You drop it.
