You are in a Dry Path.

There is a narrow path on the ground here running west to northeast.  The desert seems to fade heading toward the northeast.  You could also go west from here, back into the large desert.

On the path, you see a little knob of wood poking out of the ground.  It looks like it might be a root, but you don't see a tree anywhere for miles.

> use water on root

> use water on root
You poor the little bit of water you have from the glass bowl onto the tiny, dry root.  You hear a slurping sound and a second of silence.

The ground begins to shake violently.  The rumble brings you to your knees.  The ground begins to split.  You fear that the Earth could open up and swallow you at any moment.  Slowly the quaking ground slows and you are able to regain your footing.

You look around and notice that off toward the southwest you see an enormous tree scraping the clear desert sky.
