> south

> south
The wire that you are carrying trails its way back toward the doctor's office.

You are in a laboratory room.

This must have been the doctors workroom.  You're surprised that it looks less like a laboratory and more like a fancy parlor you'd find in a mansion deep in the old south.  There's a pair of nice leather couches here surrounding a small table.

There is a fireplace on the western wall that catches your attention.

> in

> in

You are in a chimney.

You are inside a nice, tidy fireplace.  You can see an exit leading out and when you look up, you can see the sky above you.  It looks like you could climb this chimney, too.

It looks like you might be able to climb up from here and you certainly could go back out into the laboratory/parlor area.

The wire that you are carrying trails its way back into the laboratory.
> up

> up

You are in a Doctors office rooftop.

You are on top of the rooftop of the doctor's office.  The shingles are fairly new here and the roof seems to be in much better shape than the buildings that surround you.

There is a chimney here that you could probably squeeze back down if you wanted to.  There is also a cylidrical scaffolding attached to the western portion of this roof, but it appears that it has fallen over to the roof of the building to your west.

The wire that you are carrying trails its way back into the chimney down toward the doctors office.
> west

> west

You are in a Sheriffs Office Roof.

You are on top of the sheriff's office roof.  Be careful where you step because this roof seems to be in pretty bad shape.  There is an opening here where you could climb back down into the office.
If you can tightrope walk, you probably could cross the metal scaffolding that is connecting this roof to the roof to the east.

The wire that you are carrying moves across the busted scaffolding to the roof to the east.
> down

> down

 You are  on top of the sheriff's desk.

You are standing on the desk in the sheriff's office.  From here, you could 'get off desk' or 'climb down' back to the floor of the sheriff's office.

After moving the desk you could probably reach the access panel on the ceiling as well.

> climb down

> climb down

You are in a Sheriffs Office.

This sheriff's office doesn't seem to have been used for a VERY long time.  Cobwebs cling to every corner of the room.  There is a thick layer of dust laying undisturbed on the desk.  The desk has been moved to the eastern wall of the room, directly above which is an access panel.

The wire that you are carrying disappears through the opening in the roof.
> north

> north

You are in a Jail.

You are in a very small room.  In the southwest corner of this room is a small cell.  The door is standing ajar and it looks like you could easily go into the cell.

The wire that you are carrying leads back into the sheriff's office.
> in

> in

You are in a prison cell.

This room is dark and drab.  There is a slab of wood securely fastened to the floor here that you could only imagine was once a bed for whatever prisoner was the guest.  The slots in the iron bars are just large enough for you to fit your skinny arms through but that's about it.

There is a door leading back out into the jail room.

As you move into the jail cell, you have reached the end of the line of wire.
> tie wire to cell door

> tie wire to cell door
