You are in a Bank.

You are in a bank.  On the northern side of the room, there is a continuous counter that forms a U-shape and there are three places along the counter where tellers used to stand.  There is a sign at each teller stand that says "Closed - See your next available teller please."

To the west, stands an open door that leads out into the town square.  To the southeast, you see a closed door that reads "Office" on a small centered plaque.  To the northeast, you see a large metal vault with a keypad offset to the right of it.

> push green button

> push green button
After a moment, you hear a click, followed by a robotic female voice.

"Hello, patron of the bank.  I am Velma.  I am the Vault Electronic Lookout Maintenance Assistor.

Please answer the following:  What is the correct four digit password?  Please answer now."
> answer 5326

> answer 5326
You speak your answer into the keypad.
"Thank you," replies Velma.

The vault door quietly slides open granting access to the fault.
> northeast

> northeast

You are in a Vault.

You are in a bank vault.  Considering all of the work you had to do to get in here, you expected there to be piles of gold or stacks of hundred dollar bills.  But, unfortunately, neither is here. The only thing in the room is a small chest.

> use gold key on durable chest

> use gold key on durable chest
You hear a faint click.  You take a deep breath and open the small chest.
The inside of the chest is covered in smooth velvet.  Inside the chest you see a spyglass.
