You are in an Archeological Site.

It looks like this archaelogical dig site has been vacated recently.  About twenty smaller areas have already been excavated.  These small holes in the ground are all empty and vary in size from knee deep to small swimming pool size.  The dirt removed from the holes is piled up next to each hole.

There is undisturbed ground here, too.  The ground is expansive to say the least.  It probably stretches out in an area that is five or six hundred meters square.  The ground in this area is hard and slightly discolored in spots.

New to this area is the biggest tree you have ever seen.

There are exits far off to the east, southeast, and north.

> throw rope at bough

> throw rope at bough
You sling the rock end of the rope up at the bough.  The rock sails over the branch and back down toward the ground.  Fortunately you were smart enough to hold on to the non-rock side of the rope.  You tie the other end of the rope to the dangling rock.  You have now successfully created a climbing rope.  You can now climb the tree!
> up

> up
You climb the tree carefully.

You are in a First big branch.

You are standing on the first big branch of the biggest tree you have ever seen.  This is about as high as you have ever climbed a tree and there is quite possibly hundreds of feet left to the top of the tree.

You look around and it appears that you could continue climbing upward into the tree.  There is also a rope here where you could easily climb back down the tree.

> up

> up
You climb up the tree.  It seems like you've climbed forever.

You are in a Half Way Up the Giant Tree.

You are about half way up the biggest tree you have ever seen.  The view from here would be great if it weren't obstructed by all of the branches.

It appears you could climb up or down from here.  It also appears you could head out on one of the larger branches here.

> up

> up
You move slowly but confidently through the tree for what seems like hours.

You are in an Uppermost Bough.

You are at the highest substantial branch in the tree.  The wind is really strong up here and the tree sways four or five feet with each gust.  The branches in all directions are very thick so you still can't see a whole lot from here.

If you are careful, you might be able to shimmy up the trunk of this tree.  You could also climb back down, too.

> up

> up
Whew.  You grip a hold of the tree and climb up the tree very, very slowly.

You are in a Top of Giant Tree.

You are perched at the top of a giant tree perhaps three or four hundred feet above the floor of the dig site far below.  The wind pitches the top of the tree from side to side and you cling to the tree with all of your might.  What in the world are you doing up here? you wonder.

If you are brave enough to look around, the sights are amazing!

> use spyglass

> use spyglass

You put the spyglass to your eye and peer out to the northeast at the strange walled building.  You still see the black robed figures guarding the southern gate.  Each of them has a large "D" on their robes.  This entrance looks impossible to gain passage through.

But, with the aid of the spyglass, you watch the men within the walls.  In the northeast corner of the compound you see a man appear to disappear through the wall and a minute or so later re-emerge outside of the compound.  You continue watching him.  He wanders to the east where he meets a second man.  The second man lifts the rock he was leaning against and you see a keypad with bright red numbers under the rock.  He punches in the number '28744' and enter.  This man then walks to the northeast corner of the compound, touches the wall, passes through the wall and emerges on the inside.

You take a deep breath and ... you suddenly feel a little stronger... a little smarter... a little tougher.  You look back at your accomplishments so far and can't help but grin.  There's work to be done yet but you are definitely moving in the right direction.

A Man Card has been added to your inventory.

