On the path, you see a little knob of wood poking out of the ground.  It looks like it might be a root, but you don't see a tree anywhere for miles.

> northeast

> northeast

You are on an a Dirt Path.

It looks like a well travelled dirt path.  You see some vehicle tracks on the ground.  You are certainly no expert tracker, but it looks like you see some big boot prints and some worn paths that look like they have been frequently used by large, large vehicles.

Massive, unclimbable rocks wall off your path to the south and a thicket of tangled, lifeless trees and thorny shrubs are to your north and east.

You could return to the southwest and if you are dumb enough, you could try and creep to the north and follow those tracks. There is a thicket here to the east.

