You are in a Northeast Corner of Base.

You've made your way to the northeast corner of the base.  A wall runs a really long way to the west and to the south.

Just to your right, off the faint path is a large boulder.

> use lever on large boulder

> use lever on large boulder
Your high school physical science teacher would be so proud...

You wedge one end of the lever under the rock and push down really, really hard on the other end.  Unfortunately, this is not enough force to flip or lift the rock.  What now?
> jump on lever

> jump on lever
You climb up the lever and carefully walk to the end that is pointing skyward.  You jump as high as you can and come down on the end of the plank.  In a split second, the plank bends under your weight and snaps sending you tumbling to the ground.  You sit up a bit dejected that your contraption didn't work, but when you glance at the rock to give it your dirtiest look... you smile and see it has been flipped clean over revealing a security pad underneath!
> type 28744

> type 28744
You punch in the numbers 2-8-7-4-4 and press enter.  At first you think nothing is happening, but almost like a whisper in the wind, you hear a very faint vibration at your feet.  Then all is quiet again.  You think it came from the junction of the two giant walls of the base.

Also, from the corner of your eye you see a ring of dust float in the air from that direction.

> stand on circle

> stand on circle
You stand on the circle of dirt.  You feel like you are on the precipice of something dangerous but essential to your quest.  You take a deep breath and try to calm your nerves.

When standing on the circle, you notice a loose piece of the wall within arms reach in front of you.
> push loose section

> push loose section
You push the loose section of wall and the ground vibrates softly, followed by a *thunk* that feels like it vibrated the soles of your shoes.  The ground dips and you begin to sink into the desert floor.  You consider hopping off the platform, but because of that fancy Man Card you have, you decide to wait it out.

Slowly you disappear into the ground.  You continue to move downward for what you estimate is about ten feet and then the platform slides forward.  After a few seconds the platform once again stops and you begin to move upward.  The moment is here...

As your eyes rise above the level of the ground, you take a look around and your heart sinks.  You are surrounded, I mean completely surrounded, by Dingo's evil henchmen.

You are in a Guard Barracks.

You have finally made it inside the enemy compound with the intent of completing the mission entrusted to Agent Straussberger, but here apparently is where your dream of being something other, and more important, than what you really are comes to an end.

This is the guard barracks.  You are currently surrounded by Dingo's evil henchmen.  What will you do?

